<br>
*They all fought bravely, and held their own. Thurdolor, Iyiro, and Reine were busy with their demons, while the groups of 5 had their own. The group of 5 circled around, backs to each other, and faught off the demons. Kenyon fell to his knees from fatigue. Pops made a barrier with his magic, and forced the demons back a bit, but pops was too old. His barrier gave way soon after, and the demons resumed their attack. The otehrs tried to help, but their demon foes were not giving them the chance too. Eventually the group of 5 fell, and they were all killed. Pops, Kenyon, Ryngo, Bulkor, and Kenjo were all dead. Now the group was facing 10 demons, and only 8 (Iyiro, Thurdolor, Reine, the 4 guards and 1 mage) of them were left to fight this new threat.* <p>Don't fear that which you do not know I wont hurt you</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bgoergyboysroleplayingpalace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goergyboy>Goergyboy</A> at: 10/6/03 6:29 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bgoergyboysroleplayingpalace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=clockworkmist>Clockwork Mist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#0000FF>(10/6/03 10:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crises of Nygard part 1- The Beginning of Legend</span><hr size=1> Iyiro fought his demon till the 5 had died.  He faded into the middle where the other two were and grimaced slightly with some caution, &quot;doesn't look good...&quot;<br>
<br>
Iyiro pressed the button on the end of his grip, and the sword extended into whip form.  He swung it methodically and then lunged it forward to a demon, catching it would be more stupid than sweeping the desert.  Even with steel palms, it would surely leave a nice gash.  But if it weren't blocked it would sending one demon into hell where it belongs.  <br>
<br>
He wasn't sure if this would work, but as a double up, he flung his lashknife free with his other hand and swung it towards a second demon.  Using both weapons like a pirate steers a ship.  Both would deal certain death, or perhaps wound severely. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bgoergyboysroleplayingpalace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=coolrain@goergyboysroleplayingpalace>coolrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#0000FF>(10/6/03 6:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crises of Nygard part 1- The Beginning of Legend</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://.<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.gamespy.com/avatars/av/MA/ma148" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END-->[/img]<br>
